HEADWORD: greasewood
<hw>greasewood</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A low hardy much-branched spiny
shrub (<spn>Sarcobatus vermiculatus</spn>) common in alkaline soils of
Western America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> black greasewood, <spn>Sarcobatus
vermiculatus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

